                            <comment id="157122" author="adilger" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2016 15:12:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My bad. This is related to patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/20465&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/20465&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7334&quot; title=&quot;Refactor lprocfs helpers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7334&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7334&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lov: Cleanup lov_stripe proc files&quot; because I thought those /proc files were left over from the lod/lov split. I think that patch should be reverted. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
